prompt.transcript:
42yo, P1 - CS, 38+2, BMI 26.5, Rh+ve

Attended with DFM

HPC
Clinically well
No SROM/PVB/abn discharge
Slight reduction in FM today
Attended MAU
Ix reassuringly N (obs/urine/CTG)

Was awaiting clinic appt this afternoon to discuss timing of planned CS

Bedside scan by MAU lead midwife as part of learning to do presentation scanning under my (SpR Nouvel) guidance
Baby transverse, head on maternal right, back up, DVP 4.5cm, nothing in the pelvis (no feet, no cord)

Discussed transverse presentation at term
Offered admission 
Explained risk of cord prolapse: with SROM would be very risky, need an emergency CS
If out of hospital, assume 'child's pose', explained position, call triage and ambulance
Offered earlier CS - agreed tomorrow, booked
Consented for CS
Eilidh keen on staying in for a few hours, then home to sleep, back in the morning, will call if anything transpires.
